-- Jacob Rothschild Names Kestenbaum to Head His Five Arrows Group, FT Says
-- B y   A l a n   P u r k i s s
-- 2010-10-18T07:17:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-18/jacob-rothschild-names-kestenbaum-to-head-his-five-arrows-group-ft-says.html
Jacob Rothschild, a U.K. investor
and philanthropist, named  Jonathan Kestenbaum , 49, to succeed
him as chairman and chief executive officer of Five Arrows Ltd.,
his family investment company, the Financial Times reported.  Kestenbaum is currently the CEO of the National Endowment
for Science, Technology and the Arts, a publicly owned body
charged with investing a 200 million-pound ($477 million)
endowment in promising technology companies, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alan Purkiss  in London on   apurkiss@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge in London at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 